  "prompt": "What is fossil fuel?",
  "response": "Fossil fuels are non-renewable energy sources formed from the decomposition of dead plants and animals over millions of years. They include:\n\n1. Coal\n- Formed from dead plant matter\n- Used for electricity generation\n- Highest carbon emissions\n\n2. Oil (Petroleum)\n- Formed from marine organisms\n- Used for transportation and manufacturing\n- Refined into gasoline, diesel, and other products\n\n3. Natural Gas\n- Formed alongside oil deposits\n- Used for heating, cooking, and electricity generation\n- Cleaner burning compared to coal and oil\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Formed over millions of years\n- Non-renewable resources\n- High carbon dioxide emissions\n- Major contributor to climate change\n- Primarily extracted through mining and drilling\n\nWhen burned, fossil fuels release energy but also produce greenhouse gases that contribute to global warming. Many countries are now seeking alternative renewable energy sources like solar, wind, and hydroelectric power to reduce fossil fuel dependence.",
